Here are some good articles on video game design for the age group we are focusing on that I've found:

http://www.pbs.org/parents/childrenandmedia/videogames-preschool.html
* Mostly just conceptual advice here, but some good things to keep in mind

http://www.sproutonline.com/games
http://pbskids.org/games
http://www.nickjr.com/games/
http://www.fisher-price.com/en_US/gamesandactivities/onlinegames/index.html
http://www.learn4good.com/games/kids.htm
http://www.kidsgames.org/
* There are a lot of actual games here that we can model new designs after

http://www.fisher-price.com/en_US/parenting-articles/playtime-and-toys/what-do-young-kids-learn-from-playing-games
http://www.bbc.com/news/health-28602887
http://mediasmarts.ca/video-games/video-games-special-issues-young-children
* Some good info here on what we're trying to achieve through with educational video games


